<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="506" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[781,1379,397,824]" pageId="22" pageNumber="506">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koopman &amp; E. E. Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[791,1032,555,588]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">Tonatia saurophila</taxonomicName>
was originally described from fossil material recovered in a cave in 
<collectingCountry box="[781,896,633,666]" name="Jamaica" pageId="22" pageNumber="506">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
and later found alive in Central America; this subspecies is now considered extinct. S. L. Williams and collaborators in 1995 revised 7 
<taxonomicName box="[1050,1134,752,785]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Tonatia</taxonomicName>
and recognized 
<taxonomicName box="[791,968,791,824]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">1. saurophila</taxonomicName>
as distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[1249,1373,791,824]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Thymelaeaceae" genus="Lophostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="22" pageNumber="506" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bidens">71. bidens</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[171,1381,830,2244]" pageId="22" pageNumber="506">
Thus, references to 
<taxonomicName box="[456,566,830,863]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Thymelaeaceae" genus="Lophostoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="22" pageNumber="506" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bidens">1. bidens</taxonomicName>
from Central America and northern South America apply to 
<taxonomicName box="[215,382,869,902]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="506" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">1. saurophila</taxonomicName>
. Two extant subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
